Bank Management System
This project simulates a simple banking system with credit and debit in bank accounts. The project is implemented in C language and uses file handling to store data and user information. The following basic operations are supported:

Credit
Debit
Check balance
Close account
Getting Started
These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

Prerequisites
A C compiler
A text editor
Installing
Clone the repository to your local machine:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/[username]/bank-management-system.git
Open the main.c file in a text editor and compile it using a C compiler.

Usage
The program will prompt the user to choose an operation to perform. The user can choose from the following operations:

Credit
Debit
Check balance
Close account
After the operation is performed, the user will be prompted to choose another operation or exit the program.

File Handling
The program uses file handling to store the data and user information. The data is stored in a binary file using the fwrite function and read from the file using the fread function.

Error Handling
The program includes error handling for cases where the file cannot be opened or read from. In such cases, an error message is displayed and the program continues to run.

Built With
C language
File handling in C
